    <description>
        <p>
            Keyguard is a multi-client for the Bitwarden速 platform and KeePass (KDBX), created to provide the best user experience possible.
        </p>
        <p>
            Can be used with any Bitwarden速 installation. This product is not associated with the Bitwarden project nor Bitwarden, Inc. Bitwarden速 is a registered trademark of Bitwarden Inc.
        </p>
        <p>
            <em>Highlights</em>
            <ul>
                <li>a beautiful rich and responsive
                    <em>Material You</em> user interface
                </li>
                <li>a
                    <em>powerful</em> and
                    <em>fast search</em>
                </li>
                <li>a watchtower that finds items with
                    <em>Pwned passwords</em>,
                    <em>Vulnerable accounts</em>,
                    <em>Reused passwords</em>,
                    <em>Inactive two factor authentication</em>,
                    <em>Inactive passkeys</em>,
                    <em>Unsecure Websites</em> as well as
                    <em>Duplicate</em>,
                    <em>Incomplete</em> and
                    <em>Expiring</em> items, and other
                </li>
                <li>
                    <em>multi-account support</em> with secure login and two-factor authentication support
                </li>
                <li>add items and sends _(Bitwarden)_, modify, and view your vault
                    <em>offline</em>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <em>export individual</em> or organization items,
                    <em>including the attachments</em>
                </li>
                <li>beautiful
                    <em>Light</em>/
                    <em>Dark theme</em>
                </li>
                <li>a generator with
                    <em>SSH keys</em>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <em>Email forwarders</em>
                </li>
                <li>a support for shortcuts, placeholders and URL overrides</li>
                <li>a smart conflict resolution</li>
                <li>and much more!</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </description>
